    "source_sections": {
      "references": "",
      "remarks": "It is easy to see that $h(n)=n+1$ if and only if $n+1$ is prime, and that $h(n)$ is unbounded for odd $n$. \n\nIt is probably true that $h(n)=3$ for infinitely many $n$.\n\nSee also [820]."
    },
